7
00:00:26.600 --> 00:00:30.160
In this chapter, we will be working on a few DAX calculations.

8
00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:32.080
To summarise.

9
00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:35.840
Calculated columns evaluate each row.

10
00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:43.960
It adds a new column to an existing table and is calculated at data load or when the data is refreshed.

11
00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:48.240
As you can see in the example, a TotalYTD() function is used for

12
00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:54.240
aggregating the year-to-date sales value of the expression in the current context.

13
00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:58.320
Whereas measures aggregate multiple rows.

14
00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:02.480
Results in another field can be added to your visualization

15
00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:07.960
and are calculated at query time as you interact and filter.

16
00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:11.400
As you can see in the example, Profit is calculated by

17
00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:15.760
